| Lab IGI | F-VVS2 | [$1,600](https://www.bluenile.com/lab-diamond-search?Shape=Oval&Carats=2&Color=F&Clarity=VVS2&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [$3,625](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=vintage&ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [$3,170](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=vintage&ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) | [$3,915](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=vintage&ShapeID=Oval&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) |

**Note on color grading for vintage settings:** Yellow gold vintage settings mask color down to J. Platinum or white gold settings require G or better for a colorless appearance. If you are buying a vintage ring in yellow gold (a period-correct choice), you can safely go to H-I color and save $2,000–$4,000 on a 2ct diamond without any visible compromise.

---

## Metal Choice for Vintage Oval Rings

**Platinum:** Period-correct for Art Deco and Edwardian. The highest density metal (21.45 g/cm³) means it wears without rhodium plating and develops a natural patina over time — a characteristic many vintage buyers actively want. Platinum vintage settings from Blue Nile price [$200–$400 more than white gold equivalents](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings?styleIDs=vintage&a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Worth the premium for authenticity.

**Yellow Gold:** The most period-correct choice for Victorian and Art Nouveau designs. The warm tone complements the carved, organic detailing of scrollwork and leaf patterns. The [Garland Sapphire setting at $3,670](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/garland-sapphire-and-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-195061?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) looks most authentic in yellow gold.

**Rose Gold:** A modern romantic interpretation that reads as vintage without being period-accurate. Rose gold with milgrain and engraving is a wildly popular combination for engagement rings specifically because it feels simultaneously warm and antique. Not historically accurate — rose gold was not widely used in Edwardian or Art Deco settings — but visually beautiful.

**White Gold:** Looks like platinum at lower cost. Requires rhodium plating every 1–3 years. For vintage rings that you expect to wear daily for decades, platinum is a more practical choice despite the upfront cost.

---

> "The most frequent mistake I see with vintage oval rings is buyers choosing a setting so ornate that the diamond gets lost in the metalwork. A vintage setting should frame the oval — not compete with it. My rule: if the setting has more than two layers of visual detail (e.g., halo + pavé band + engraving), consider a larger center stone to maintain balance. A 1.5ct oval in an ornate setting often reads smaller than a 1.2ct oval in a clean milgrain solitaire."
>
> — **Farzana Hasan**, GIA-Certified Diamond Expert, DiamondCritics.com

---

## Final Verdict

The [Infinity Vintage-Style by James Allen at $2,025](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/infinity-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315141?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the statistically validated choice — 202 reviews representing real buyers who chose this ring for oval diamonds and reported satisfaction. Its intertwining pavé shank naturally echoes the elongated oval outline in a way that makes the ring look like it was designed specifically for this shape.

For buyers with a specific era target: Art Deco buyers should start with the [Fleur-De-Lis Pavé at $1,570](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/art-deco-inspired-fleur-de-lis-pave-vintage-style-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-315295?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) (best value in the category). Milgrain purists should choose the [Hand-Engraved Micropavé at $2,315](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/hand-engraved-micropave-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-1-6-ct-tw-item-194236?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Buyers seeking rose cut or old mine cut ovals need to go beyond Blue Nile entirely.

